Emirati Women's Day receives great attention from our leader, His Highness,
Sheikh/Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan…
and his brothers, the rulers of the emirates.
On this day, Emirati women are being celebrated …
As a sign of appreciation for their efforts and their effective role in serving the community and their country.
Over the past years, I have worked in governmental departments and saved no effort, and was fully dedicated.
At present, I am working in the private sector, for one of the topnotch companies in the country…
DSV company …
The company always appreciates my efforts and performance.
Emirati Women's Day comes to remind me of my contribution and duties towards my community…
as a volunteer, a photographer…
and the leader of the Emirate of Dubai in one of the national programs of response to emergencies and rescue.
Emirati Women's Day comes to remind me of my duties and my effective contributions to society, such as my work.
Emirati Women's Day comes to remind me of my effective contribution in serving my community and in serving my homeland…
The contribution that I still make in several fields as a volunteer…
and a trainer in the SANED program in several fields.
As a volunteer, international first aider, photographer, and trainer in the SANED program…
the Emergency Response Program…
Emirati Women's Day has a special place in my heart…
On that day I feel proud and that I’m appreciated…
for all my accomplishments.
Happy Emirati Women's Day.
